Welcome! We are excited you're interested in helping build the ultimate AI companion. To ensure a smooth process for everyone, please follow these guidelines.
1. How to Report Bugs
If you find something broken, please open a new issue on GitHub and:
Use the label bug.
Provide a clear, descriptive title (e.g., "Deep Search Mode crashes on mobile screens").
Describe the steps to reproduce the bug (e.g., click sequence, input prompt).
Include your operating system and browser versions.
2. Suggesting Features
We welcome new ideas! If you want to propose a significant new feature or enhancement:
Open an issue with the label enhancement.
Explain the "why"â€”what problem does this feature solve for the user?
Describe the proposed solution and how it fits into the existing UI (e.g., a new button, a setting, a new chat mode).
3. Contributing Code
For code contributions, please follow the Forking Workflow:
Fork the repository to your own GitHub account.
Clone your fork locally: git clone https://github.com/[YOUR-USERNAME]/popking-ai.git
Create a new branch for your feature or fix (e.g., git checkout -b feature/tts-speaker-select).
Make your changes, following the established file structure and style (e.g., use modern React hooks, Tailwind CSS).
Commit your changes with clear, descriptive messages.
Push your branch to your fork.
Open a Pull Request (PR) against the main branch of the official PopKing AI repository.
Pull Request (PR) Requirements:
Single Focus: PRs should address a single bug or feature.
Tests: If applicable, include unit tests for new or changed logic.
Documentation: Update the README.md or any relevant internal comments if your change impacts usage or functionality.
4. Code Style & Standards
We use the following standards:
Language: JavaScript/TypeScript (React).
Styling: Tailwind CSS only.
Functionality: Use modern functional components and hooks.
Comments: Use JSDoc-style comments for complex functions and API interfaces.
Thank you for contributing 
